obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (36712)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, commencement and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00016_196152_1517807321778&sectionId=36712&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00016_196152_1517807321778
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the`
  line `Apprentices Act, 1961.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1`
  line ***.
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different States.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this Act shall not apply to`
  line
  line `(a) any area or to any industry in any area unless the Central Government by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette specifies that area or industry as an area or industry to which the said provisions shall`
  line `apply with effect from such date as may be mentioned in the notification;`
  line
  line ^3
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(c) any such special apprenticeship scheme for imparting training to apprentices as may be`
  line `notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 25 of 1968, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-8-1968).`
  line
  line `2. 1st March, 1962, vide notification No. G.S.R. 246, dated 12th February, 1962, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (b) omitted by Act 27 of 1973, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-12-1974).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 1-12-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (36713)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00016_196152_1517807321778&sectionId=36713&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00016_196152_1517807321778
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "All India Council" means the All India Council of Technical Education established by the`
  line `resolution of the Government of India in the former Ministry of Education No. F. 16-10/44-E.III,`
  line `dated the 30th November, 1945;]`
  line
  line `^2[(aa)] "apprentice" means a person who is undergoing apprenticeship training ^3`
  line `*** in pursuance`
  line `of a contract of apprenticeship;`
  line
  line `^1[(aaa) "apprenticeship training" means a course of training in any industry or establishment`
  line `undergone in pursuance of a contract of apprenticeship and under prescribed terms and conditions`
  line `which may be different for different categories of apprentices;]`
  line
  line `(b) "Apprenticeship Adviser" means the Central Apprenticeship Adviser appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 26 or the State Apprenticeship Adviser appointed under sub-section (2) of`
  line `that section;`
  line
  line `(c) "Apprenticeship Council" means the Central Apprenticeship Council or the State`
  line `Apprenticeship Council established under sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(d) "appropriate Government" means,--`
  line
  line `(1) in relation to--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Apprenticeship Council, or`
  line
  line `^4[(aa) the Regional Boards, or`
  line
  line `(aaa) the practical training of graduate or technician apprentices or technician`
  line `(vocational) apprentices, or]`
  line
  line `(b) any establishment of any railway, major port, mine or oil field, or`
  line
  line `^5[(bb) any establishment which is operating business or trade from different locations`
  line `situated in four or more States, or]`
  line
  line `(c) any establishment owned, controlled or managed by--`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Government or a department of the Central Government,`
  line
  line `(ii) a company in which not less than fifty-one per cent. of the share capital is held by`
  line `the Central Government or partly by that Government and partly by one or more State`
  line Governments,
  line
  line `(iii) a corporation (including a co-operative society) established by or under a Central`
  line `Act which is owned, controlled or managed by the Central Government,`
  line
  line `the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(2) in relation to--`
  line
  line `(a) a State Apprenticeship Council, or`
  line
  line `(b) any establishment other than an establishment specified in sub-clause (1) of this`
  line clause,
  line
  line `the State Government;`
  line
  line `^6[(dd) "Board or State Council of Technical Education" means the Board or State Council of`
  line `Technical Education established by the State Government;]`
  line
  line `^7[(e) "designated trade" means any trade or occupation or any subject field in engineering or`
  line `non-engineering or technology or any vocational course which the Central Government, after`
  line `consultation with the Central Apprenticeship Council, may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify as a designated trade for the purposes of this Act;]`
  line
  line `(f) "employer" means any person who employs one or more other persons to do any work in an`
  line `establishment for remuneration and includes any person entrusted with the supervision and control of`
  line `employees in such establishment;`
  line
  line `(g) "establishment" includes any place where any industry is carried on ^8[and where an`
  line `establishment consists of different departments or have branches, whether situated in the same place`
  line `or at different places, all such departments or branches shall be treated as part of that establishment];`
  line
  line `(h) "establishment in private sector" means an establishment which is not an establishment in`
  line `public sector;`
  line
  line `(i) "establishment in public sector" means an establishment owned, controlled or managed by--`
  line
  line `(1) the Government or a department of the Government;`
  line
  line `(2) a Government company as defined in section 617 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(3) a corporation (including a co-operative society) established by or under a Central,`
  line `Provincial or State Act, which is owned, controlled or managed by the Government;`
  line
  line `(4) a local authority;`
  line
  line `^9[(j) "graduate or technician apprentice" means an apprentice who holds, or is undergoing training`
  line `in order that he may hold a degree or diploma in engineering or non-engineering or technology or`
  line `equivalent qualification granted by any institution recognised by the Government and undergoes`
  line `apprenticeship training in any designated trade;`
  line
  line `(k) "industry" means any industry or business in which any trade, occupation or subject field in`
  line `engineering or non-engineering or technology or any vocational course may be specified as a`
  line `designated trade or optional trade or both;]`
  line
  line `(l) "National Council" means the National Council for Training in Vocational Trades established`
  line `by the resolution of the Government of India in the Ministry of Labour (Directorate General of`
  line `Resettlement and Employment) No. TR/E.P.24/56, dated the 21st August, 1956;`
  line `^10[and re-named as`
  line `the National Council for Vocational Training by the resolution of the Government of India in the`
  line `Ministry of Labour (Directorate-General of Employment and Training) No. DGET/12/21/80-TC,`
  line `dated the 30th September, 1981];`
  line
  line `^11[(ll) "optional trade" means any trade or occupation or any subject field in engineering or`
  line `non-engineering or technology or any vocational course as may be determined by the employer for`
  line `the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(lll) "portal-site" means a website of the Central Government for exchange of information under`
  line `this Act;]`
  line
  line `(m) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^12[(mm) "Regional Board" means any Board of Apprenticeship Training registered under the`
  line `Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) at Bombay, Calcutta, Madras or Kanpur;]`
  line
  line `(n) "State" includes a Union territory;`
  line
  line `(o) "State Council" means a State Council for Training in Vocational Trades established by the`
  line `State Government;`
  line
  line `(p) "State Government" in relation to a Union territory means the Administrator thereof;`
  line
  line `^10[(pp) "technician (vocational) apprentice" means an apprentice who holds or is undergoing`
  line `training in order that he may hold a certificate in vocational course involving two years of study after`
  line `the completion of the secondary stage of school education recognised by the All-India Council and`
  line `undergoes apprenticeship training in any ^13[designated trade];]`
  line
  line `^14[(q) "trade apprentice" means an apprentice who undergoes apprenticeship training in any`
  line `designated trade;`
  line
  line `(r) "worker" means any person working in the premises of the employer, who is employed for`
  line `wages in any kind of work either directly or through any agency including a contractor and who gets`
  line `his wages directly or indirectly from the employer but shall not include an apprentice referred to in`
  line `clause (aa).]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (a) re-lettered as clause (aa) thereof by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1974).`
  line
  line `3. The words in a designated trade omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1974).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 41 of 1986, s. 2, for item (aa) (w.e.f. 16-12-1987).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 29 of 2014, s. 2 (w.e.f. 22-12-2014).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 27 of 1973, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-12-1974).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 29 of 2014, s. 2, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 22-12-2014).`
  line
  line `8. Added by Act 4 of 1997, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-1-1997).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 29 of 2014, s. 2, for clauses (j) and (k) (w.e.f. 22-12-2014).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 41 of 1986, s. 2 (w.e.f. 16-12-1987).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 29 of 2014, s. 2 (w.e.f. 22-12-2014).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 27 of 1973, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-12-1974).`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by Act 29 of 2014, s. 2, for such subject field in any vocational course as may be prescribed (w.e.f. 22-12-2014).`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clauses (q) and (r) (w.e.f. 22-12-2014)./`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (36714)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Qualifications for being engaged as an apprentice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00016_196152_1517807321778&sectionId=36714&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00016_196152_1517807321778
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `A person shall not be qualified for being`
  line `engaged as an apprentice to undergo apprenticeship training in any designated trade, unless he--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) is not less than fourteen years of age, and for designated trades related to hazardous`
  line `industries, not less than eighteen years of age; and]`
  line
  line `(b) satisfies such standards of education and physical fitness as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that different standards may be prescribed in relation to apprenticeship training in different`
  line `designated trades ^2[and for different categories of apprentices].`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2014, s. 3, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 22-12-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Added by Act 27 of 1973, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-12-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (36754)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title `Reservation of training places for the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes in designated trades.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00016_196152_1517807321778&sectionId=36754&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00016_196152_1517807321778
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[3A. Reservation of training places for the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes in`
  line `designated trades.--(1) In every designated trade, training places shall be reserved by the employer for`
  line `the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes ^2[and where there is more than one designated trade in an`
  line `establishment, such training places shall be reserved also on the basis of the total number of apprentices in`
  line `all the designated trades in such establishment].`
  line
  line `(2) The number of training places to be reserved for the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes`
  line `under sub-section (1) shall be such as may be prescribed, having regard to the population of the`
  line `Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes in the State concerned.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, the expressions "Scheduled Castes" and "Scheduled Tribes" shall have`
  line `the meanings as in clauses (24) and (25) of article 366 of the Constitution.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 41 of 1986, s. 4 (w.e.f. 16-12-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_b:
  sectionId (36716)
  sectionNo 3B
  orderNo 5
  title `Reservation of training places for Other Backward Classes in designated trades.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 2007, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-2008).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00016_196152_1517807321778&sectionId=36716&sectionno=3B&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00016_196152_1517807321778
obj_root_law_sections_3_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[3B. Reservation of training places for Other Backward Classes in designated trades.--(1) In`
  line `every designated trade, training places shall be reserved by the employer for the Other Backward Classes`
  line `and where there is more than one designated trade in an establishment, such training places shall be`
  line `reserved also on the basis of the total number of apprentices in all the designated trades in such`
  line establishment.
  line
  line `(2) The number of training places to be reserved for the Other Backward Classes under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be such as may be prescribed, having regard to the population of the Other Backward`
  line `Classes in the State concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (36717)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 6
  title `Contract of apprenticeship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00016_196152_1517807321778&sectionId=36717&sectionno=4&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00016_196152_1517807321778
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Contract of apprenticeship.--(1) No person shall be engaged as an apprentice to undergo`
  line `apprenticeship training in a designated trade unless such person or, if he is a minor, his guardian has`
  line `entered into a contract of apprenticeship with the employer.`
  line
  line `(2) The apprenticeship training shall be deemed to have commenced on the date on which the contract`
  line `of apprenticeship has been entered into under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Every contract of apprenticeship may contain such terms and conditions as may be agreed to by`
  line `the parties to the contract:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such term or condition shall be inconsistent with any provision of this Act or any`
  line `rule made thereunder.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(4) Every contract of apprenticeship entered into under sub-section (1) shall be sent by the employer`
  line `employer within thirty days to the Apprenticeship Adviser until a portal-site is developed by the Central`
  line `Government, and thereafter the details of contract of apprenticeship shall be entered on the portal-site`
  line `within seven days, for verification and registration.`
  line
  line `(4A) In the case of objection in the contract of apprenticeship, the Apprenticeship Adviser shall`
  line `convey the objection to the employer within fifteen days from the date of its receipt.`
  line
  line `(4B) The Apprenticeship Adviser shall register the contract of apprenticeship within thirty days from`
  line `the date of its receipt.]`
  line
  line ^3
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(6) Where the Central Government, after consulting the Central Apprenticeship Council, makes any`
  line `rule varying the terms and conditions of apprenticeship training of any category of apprentices`
  line `undergoing such training, then, the terms and conditions of every contract of apprenticeship relating to`
  line `that category of apprentices and subsisting immediately before the making of such rule shall be deemed to`
  line `have been modified accordingly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1973, s. 7, for section 4 (w.e.f. 1-12-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 29 of 2014, s. 4, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 22-12-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (5) omitted by 29 of 2014, s. 4 (w.e.f. 22-12-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (36718)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 7
  title `Novation of contract of apprenticeship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00016_196152_1517807321778&sectionId=36718&sectionno=5&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00016_196152_1517807321778
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Where an employer with whom a contract of`
  line `apprenticeship has been entered into, is for any reason unable to fulfil his obligations under the contract`
  line `and with the approval of the Apprenticeship Adviser it is agreed between the employer, the apprentice or`
  line `his guardian and any other employer that the apprentice shall be engaged as an apprentice under the other`
  line `employer for the unexpired portion of the period of apprenticeship training, the agreement, on registration`
  line `with the Apprenticeship Adviser, shall be deemed to be the contract of apprenticeship between the`
  line `apprentice or his guardian and the other employer, and on and from the date of such registration, the`
  line `contract of apprenticeship with the first employer shall terminate and no obligation under that contract`
  line `shall be enforceable at the instance of any party to the contract against the other party thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (36719)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 8
  title `Regulation of optional trade.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
